## The Final Verdict

![](https://images.squarespace-cdn.com/content/v1/5d56e145f80b7500016ba502/910310ec-da9c-4a57-9c21-b43b05359b5b/processed_1000014823.jpg)

窶亀he Flash #32 is a quintessential superhero comic. It manages to be funny, relevant, and emotionally grounded while still delivering the high-octane action fans expect from the title.

窶騎yan North is clearly having the time of his life with Wally窶冱 voice, and Gavin Guidry is proving to be one of the best "acting" artists in the business. By taking a modern annoyance like "doing it for the 窶枠ram" and turning it into a legitimate tactical problem for the world窶冱 fastest man, the creative team has found a way to make the Flash feel more essential than ever.

窶紀f you窶况e been away from the Flash for a while, or if you were worried about the transition after the previous creative team窶冱 departure, this is your sign to jump back in. This isn't just a great Flash story; it窶冱 a great comic book story.

